caption: Phenomenal food, taste profiles you’ll be hard pressed to find elsewhere, and an incredible, thoughtfully designed atmosphere. Would recommend to anyone looking for a unique, engaging dining experience.

Chi Cha rebranded and turned its hooka lounge into a restaurant and a market - a great pivot during COVID. The food is Peruvian inspired. We had their pork belly sandwich - Peruvian Breakfast on the brunch menu, a Peruvian traditional soup - Aguadio de Pollo (I feel like it’s chive but menu says cilantro - it really elevates the soup), tuna ceviche (very japanese inspired and great flavor emphasizing the earthy tones through soy sauce, wasabi and seasame).  Their cocktails are worth the price and so appetizing.  We got coffee and Nutella empanadas to finish the meal. One takeaway is that, after their rebranding, they have done a great job serving Peruvian food right and well, providing a cozy and lush dinning environment, and offering a creative alternative - a market/cafe where you can grab something home quick.

WE FELT DISRESPECTED!  Pros - The hookah is really good. The drinks were all right too. Really enjoyed the music. Mature crowd.  Cons - The servers were almost always on their phones in the corner smoking hookah, with their backs turned against the customers. That is quite unprofessional in my opinion. Either hubby or I had to wait for our server to turn our way for us to get her attention for more drinks. What really made us mad is when we walked in at 5:50pm, we were told to sit anywhere, which we did. At 10:58pm, a server came to us and said, "we have to move you because we have a group that will spend $1,000 on this table" 😱🤯😡. The minimum individual spending if you want to sit on a table is $45 according to what they have indicated on their hookah menu; our bill was $156.75 so well over their minimum limit. Now this server did not know our spending capacity, or that we had a group of friends coming to join us, which we explained but that did not matter to her or the manager. They offered us 2 seats that would be joining a couple that seemed comfortable in their own space, so umm No!We did not feel like we had to move. If the group did have a reservation, we should have been made aware that the table was reserved or even if they thought we would leave early having come in so early, an option to move to a different table of our choosing earlier in the night, when seats were available, would have been disappointing but sufficed. We were asked to move when the group was already in the doors and already getting upset that they had to wait. No offer to reduce the bill, for the inconvenience, was extended by the manager, he just said "the establishment also has its priorities for bigger groups". We were clearly not a priority and for that, it's unlikely we will ever be back. To add insult to injury, they added a $25 gratuity to the bill. P.s. we spent more that $1,500 where we went to meet our friends.  Conclusion - An okay chill spot if you don't mind unprofessionalism. Remember gratuity is included. Ask if the table is reserved for later if you go in early, so you are not abruptly and rudely asked to move.

DJ is jamming! The only issue was confusion with the reservations for tonight. We didn't make any but were welcomed and accommidated without any issues. Thx Chi-Cha lounge family!

I really enjoyed this place. Good food. I really don't smoke hookah, but it was still a great atmosphere to hang out with my friends. Table areas are comfy and I like the hip hop music they play. I'd definitely return. Getting 4 stars because the bathroom is in a tight basement area and it kind of smelled weird.
nice

Me and my girlfriend came into this place from out of town wanting to experience hookah in D.C. We sat down in the center of lounge for 15 minutes and nobody came over to wait on us. Finally we got up and asked why we weren't being served, they told us they never saw us there when we were clearly seated in view of every patron there. We immediately left to take our business elsewhere. WORST SERVICE EVER!
They had no more space bit they were still having ppl pay an entry fee. Only to get inside and be told you can stand near the bar.
Great spot if you want to smoke hookah and listen to trap music

This place suffers from the disease that many DC area night spots seem to suffer from...too many dang rules. You can't sit here. You have to book a table and spend $300 minimum. It's not very lounge-y if I have to follow ten rules before I even order a drink.
cool vibes, gets crowed and the wait can be long if you dont make a reservation. Good hookah, drinks are ok and the food not bad. The music is great if you like hip hop.

Nice atmosphere, great bday spot and hang out late night with a group of friends. Beaware there is a $5 cover charge. Depending on your group size if you get a table its a $90 minimum. So the more people you bring the merrier. Usually …

The hookah and the atmosphere is great here. It's probably my favorite hookah spot in  DC. The prices of the Sheeshah is reasonable. Only questionable thing is the price of the food. It could be a little lower.

Great music, really low cover charge. The atmosphere is lively. They have long wait times for seating and hookah. Make a reservation, if coming past 9 pm. The food is really good, try the beef empanadas.
It is good.  Tell you what, the Friday night positive vibes and old school (recent like) dj is stupendous! I will be back to hear him for certain.
I'd give it more stars if the furniture wasn't in such bad shape

Nice lounge,  good vibes.  Best time to go is Friday/ Satisfy nights.  The prices are reasonable, and the cocktails are not weak.  The best part is the hookah. Wait staff are friendly and quick to get things out,  always visible and around when you need something.  Music is on point.  Overall a good time!
The Empanadas are the best! The drinks are pretty good too! The hookah is also very GOOD!
Wednesday Verses is a must.  House band extraordinary!
Great place to go love the vibes
I used to hang out here a lot in 2003-05. It started going downhill back then but was great in its prime.
Good hookah and drinks. Chill location.
Nice cozy lounge and decent prices. Love to go to happy hour on my way home from work.

The Hookah was the best part. The mojitos were good. The food, the pita bread and cucumber sauce was good enough. I am not sure about anything else. The atmosphere was Ok. We got there just before 9pm and it was slightly crowded, but after 11 it was packed. The majority of the crowd seemed to be 30 on up.

The drinks are good. The shisha is good. The couches were old and not terribly comfortable. The staff was nice. We didn't get any food because... my god is this place overpriced. It's just not worth it. There's an entire city out there, and you can definitely find better locales, better food, and better drinks, for less money.
Celebrated my 30th birthday here and everyone had a good time I've been going back since then..great drinks and great hookah and most of all good environment.
Nice atmosphere...... Terrible service and totally over priced $300 to smoke hookah and about 4-5 drinks NEVER AGAIN!
bad hookah and couldn't change it and asked to charge for an other one if I want to change it, well you got no tips and never see us again there,
Nice environment best time to go is friday nights n saturday nights...

The wait was longer than estimated. We waited beyond the time and the manager was letting people who just walked in get seated. This is all while we stood and looked at empty tables and after numerous parties who came in after us got seated ahead the manager seated us at the empty table we looked at for over an hour. Decent food and good music but management and service could use a major upgrade.
Horrible place. Manager and staff very rude... Avoid avoid avoid!!!

Chi-Cha Lounge is a good place to smoke some hookah and enjoy a great night with friends. I do think they are overpriced and the food leaves something to be desired.  I enjoy coming due to their comfortable atmosphere and convenience when I'm in the area. But I'm not going out of my way to visit. It's other closer spots that have better hookah value and food...  But if I am in the area I will stop through. I do appreciate the music and friendly staff. I've been here several times but the latest outing was with a group of my girlfriends and we had such an awesome time....one of the best in awhile!

It had been more than 5 years since my last visit, but this is not the place I remember. I went on a Saturday evening around 9PM and it was well on it's way to being a full fledged club. There was a cover. A dress code. It was not the low key hip hook bar with a non-intrusive DJ in the corner from years past. If you want a rowdy jumping club experience like most places down on K St., then this is your place.
Really feels like a has been along U Street. Weird crowd and expensive hookah. Typically not the first place I look to go.

Admittedly I'm not a hardcore Hookah person but after recently visiting Chi-Cha Lounge, I was impressed with it.  Most of my Hookah experiences in Chicago are with places that are BYOB so I was a little shocked that you had to buy drinks.  But the drinks here weren't that expensive.  What I didn't like was the wait time.  We went on Friday night and there was almost a hr wait to get a couch area.  And when we were seated we were down in a little basement corner that was very crowded.  But the price here is better than any Hookah place I've been to in Chicago.  Most places there charge per person where this place was a flat price for everyone, which was ideal for our party.  And it was crowded with a lot of people and that was a plus too.
Very comfortable lounge with grossly overpriced Hookahs.

It had been a few years since my last visit to Chi-Cha and this time I was going for a friend's birthday dinner. They stuck us in a corner lounge with ottomans for a party of 25 scheduled for dinner, not just cocktails, which they were well aware of and had prepared set menus. Orders were mixed up, we were overcharged, and had to eat three courses off our laps. That will likely be the last time I go to Chi-Cha...

You suck. Your service is horrid. How can you take a reservation FOUR days in advance for 12 people, You repeatedly call us to confirm the reservation by calling the day of (JANUARY 26) THREE times --- YES WE'RE COMING!!!, then cannot accommodate my party when we get there. Who tries to seat a party of 12 at two tiny four tops at a hookah bar? The other FOUR members of the party are supposed to just sit with no table and just order food and drinks served on their laps? What about the hookah itself? You know... The device your business is supposed to showcase?  Your staff and management were useless and disrespectful after we asked to speak with the GM. You shouldn't arrive 20-25 minutes after we requested your presence to try to resolve this issue and you bring a snotty attitude with you. Even worse, when we ask you why you have extra tables near us that have just 6 people seated at them with room for many more,  you are ignorant enough to say "why don't we stop worrying about whats going on over here and start worrying about how we're going to solve your issue."  The manager then disappears apparently looking for tables for our guests for another 20-25 minutes with no update whatsoever. All the while the other available seating and tables are slowly filling up. Strange because we couldn't be seated until our entire party was all there together, yet this group that supposedly has a reservation for 20 can come arrive whenever they please.  I'm glad we didn't wait for you to return and decided to leave, but I'm annoyed that we even stayed as long as we did. After we left we ended up going to a real hookah bar that could accommodate our party with NO NOTICE I might add and went to PURE LOUNGE. They earned our money that evening and will again in the future if we're ever in the mood for hookah in DC. Thanks for ruining at least part of my birthday that night, but looking at the bright side, i know to never go to your establishment and tell all my associates about your "service" or lack there of... whenever hookah night is suggested.

Idk bout the other reviews I have read but I frequent this place mostly for happy hr and occasional date or two. Drinks aren't expensive. anyone who knows downtown/Adams Morgan avg drink is $10-12, that's what they charge here. Food is better than most hookah spots I been to. So if ur hungry and want to smoke this is the place. Nice atmos and nice bathrooms and the music sometimes is good but u hardily notice it anyway.

We pre gamed when we got here we had to wait a while but it was worth it. An older crowd on a Thursday evening but we had a good time. Service was slow since the bartender was new. Worth the wait id say
Great cocktails--they specialize in tasty mojitos. The small plates are good too. Hard to beat the atmosphere on weekends, unless sheesha isn't your thing.
